## Observability & Logging

### REQUIRED
- Log errors with enough context to debug (without logging sensitive data).
- Provide a single, consistent logging approach.
- Use error boundaries in UI where applicable.

### PRIVACY-AWARE
- Do not log PII unless explicitly required and justified.
- Analytics events (if any) must be consent-gated.

### FORBIDDEN
- Console logging as a production observability strategy
- Logging secrets, tokens, or full request bodies containing sensitive data
